WEBVTT

01:33.885 --> 01:34.010
- Get out of my way!

01:36.763 --> 01:37.806
Bastard!

01:38.473 --> 01:39.516
Wait, bastard!

01:42.977 --> 01:45.730
- Help!
A guy with knife is chasing me.

01:45.814 --> 01:46.731
- Get out of my way!

01:46.815 --> 01:48.024
- Lower the knife!

01:48.107 --> 01:49.859
- I'll kill you!
- Lower the knife!

01:49.943 --> 01:50.902
- He's a pervert!

01:50.985 --> 01:52.821
- I can explain.

01:52.904 --> 01:54.906
I'm a reporter from the Meicho.

01:55.824 --> 01:57.659
- Then why were you asking
my wife

01:57.742 --> 01:59.202
about her panties?

02:54.632 --> 02:56.384
- Excuse me, I'd like

02:56.467 --> 02:58.386
to make an appointment
to see your listing in Shibuya.

02:58.845 --> 03:02.265
- Miss, acquiring
property in Tokyo

03:02.348 --> 03:04.559
is a very complicated endeavor.

03:04.642 --> 03:06.519
- Yes, I'm aware of that.

03:06.603 --> 03:08.313
Could we set an appointment
for tomorrow?

03:08.855 --> 03:12.901
- I'm afraid there are many
steps that must be taken.

03:12.984 --> 03:15.987
- I've taken those steps.
I'd like to see the space.

03:16.738 --> 03:20.241
- I'm afraid
the owner of that space

03:20.325 --> 03:23.077
wouldn't be interested
in renting to you.

03:24.454 --> 03:25.830
- I see...

03:25.914 --> 03:29.375
Then I'll find someone who is.

03:29.459 --> 03:30.793
Thank you for your time.

03:32.337 --> 03:33.796
- The wire service reported

03:33.880 --> 03:35.924
this panty thief
in Kabukicho yesterday,

03:36.007 --> 03:37.508
and Maruyama-san wants
two paragraphs on it

03:37.592 --> 03:40.762
for the evening edition,
but so far, I have nothing.

03:40.845 --> 03:42.388
I've been running
around Kabukicho all morning

03:42.472 --> 03:43.890
asking women
about their panties,

03:43.973 --> 03:45.058
and I almost got killed.

03:45.141 --> 03:47.477
- I have not slept in two days.

03:47.560 --> 03:49.479
- Yeah, but you got
a story published, right?

03:49.562 --> 03:51.189
- About traffic safety.
- Still a story.

03:51.272 --> 03:56.402
Every one I turned in, nope.
Tears apart.

03:56.486 --> 03:57.862
Meanwhile, I got my own story.

03:57.946 --> 03:59.489
It's better than any
of this stuff.

04:01.616 --> 04:04.994
You remember that guy who set
himself on fire in Shinjuku?

04:05.078 --> 04:07.038
- Hmm. Yeah.

04:07.121 --> 04:11.501
- I think that he's connected
to that stabbing I covered.

04:11.584 --> 04:13.795
- And by covered, you mean
wrote up as a murder

04:13.878 --> 04:17.423
so Baku almost fired you?

04:17.507 --> 04:20.134
"Gaijin! Gaijin!"

04:20.218 --> 04:22.470
- You like busting my balls,
huh?

04:22.553 --> 04:24.639
It is the great joy of my life.

04:24.722 --> 04:26.933
- All right.

04:27.016 --> 04:31.437
I gotta go. Clock's ticking.

04:55.753 --> 04:57.338
- Hey, Pol.

04:57.422 --> 04:58.131
- I have emergency.

04:58.214 --> 05:00.341
- Are you stuck
at Akira's again?

05:00.425 --> 05:02.343
Rat bastard can't put you
in a fucking cab?

05:02.427 --> 05:05.680
- Stop.
He is love of my life.

05:05.763 --> 05:08.224
I need help to pick a birthday
present for one of my regulars.

05:08.307 --> 05:11.936
- Kimchi breath guy?
- No, Hasegawa-san.

05:12.020 --> 05:13.479
- Oh.
Hairy eyebrows, close talker.

05:13.563 --> 05:14.564
- Yes.

05:14.647 --> 05:18.192
I buy him good present,
he buy champagne all night.

05:18.276 --> 05:19.569
Please, I beg you.

05:19.652 --> 05:21.654
You have taste
that is so good.

05:21.738 --> 05:22.363
- Sure. I gotta stop by Onyx.

05:22.447 --> 05:24.365
I'll meet you in Shibuya
at00?

05:24.449 --> 05:26.784
- What are you doing now?

05:26.868 --> 05:28.870
Fuck!
- I gotta go. I'll meet you.

05:31.456 --> 05:35.543
- I've been chased by worse
than a man with a knife.

05:35.626 --> 05:37.045
It's a hazard of the job.

05:37.128 --> 05:39.130
- I understand that,
Maruyama-san.

05:39.213 --> 05:42.633
I just need a little more time.

05:42.717 --> 05:45.428
- You have until00 p.m.
No later.

05:45.511 --> 05:48.890
- I-I-I-I don't have the lead.
I don't have anything.

05:48.973 --> 05:51.476
Everyone I speak to, they don't
know shit about this and--

05:51.559 --> 05:53.061
- Jake, Jake.

05:53.144 --> 05:54.854
Stop walking.

05:56.814 --> 06:00.568
Now, step back and think.

06:00.651 --> 06:02.445
Who else can you go to?

06:16.000 --> 06:17.335
- Miyamoto-san.

06:17.418 --> 06:18.961
- "I just have to have to say

06:19.045 --> 06:21.297
I find your dress
extraordinarily flattering."

06:21.380 --> 06:23.674
- It worked, right?
That was a good line, right?

06:23.758 --> 06:25.259
- Yeah.

06:25.343 --> 06:26.761
- Hey, no one knows
Kabukicho like you, right?

06:26.844 --> 06:28.429
- Well, true.

06:28.513 --> 06:29.097
- Do you know anything
about this panty thief?

06:29.180 --> 06:31.307
- Panty thief?

06:31.390 --> 06:33.309
- Do you know anything?

06:33.392 --> 06:35.686
'Cause I've been writing this
story and I--I got no leads.

06:38.940 --> 06:40.942
- I shouldn't tell you this,

06:41.025 --> 06:44.153
and if you quote me,
I'll deny it.

06:44.237 --> 06:44.779
- Okay.

06:44.862 --> 06:49.033
- There's no panty thief.

06:49.117 --> 06:50.785
- Really?

06:50.868 --> 06:54.080
- Some ladies lost
their underwear to a windy day.

06:54.163 --> 06:55.665
Wire service wrote it up

06:55.748 --> 06:59.961
because papers love a story
about a pervert.

07:00.044 --> 07:01.546
- Thank you. Wait, wait.

07:01.629 --> 07:03.714
Anyone else know about this?
- No one yet.

07:03.798 --> 07:05.383
Thank you, thank you.

07:05.466 --> 07:05.800
Thank you.

07:05.883 --> 07:07.677
Miyamoto-san.

07:29.991 --> 07:30.992
- Rewrite it.

07:31.075 --> 07:32.160
- Yes. Will do.

07:50.803 --> 07:52.013
- Rewrite it.

08:02.607 --> 08:03.524
No good.

08:26.297 --> 08:28.716
- Alright, you worthless
piece of shit.

08:31.052 --> 08:33.387
Let's try this again.

08:35.264 --> 08:39.644
You're crossing the street,
minding your own business,

08:39.727 --> 08:43.856
when this jogger comes out of
nowhere and slams into you...

08:46.817 --> 08:48.069
And?

08:48.152 --> 08:49.195
What then?

08:50.571 --> 08:51.781
- What do you want me to say?

08:53.366 --> 08:56.494
- The truth. In your words.

09:06.212 --> 09:07.463
The victim had an accidental
run-in with a thug.

09:07.546 --> 09:09.006
Wrong place, wrong time.

09:09.090 --> 09:11.425
- Funaki, you don't really
believe that.

09:11.801 --> 09:15.221
- We have his prints on the
knife and a signed deposition.

09:15.304 --> 09:17.306
What more do you want?

09:18.474 --> 09:19.892
- A low level Tozawa goon
just walks in off the street

09:19.976 --> 09:20.935
and gives himself up?

09:21.018 --> 09:22.770
Feels like the fastest way
to kill an investigation.

09:22.853 --> 09:24.689
- Investigation?

09:25.356 --> 09:28.609
Our job is to clear cases.

09:30.027 --> 09:30.528
This is going in.

09:36.534 --> 09:38.452
- That's the third shop
in the last month.

09:39.287 --> 09:41.789
All under our protection.

09:43.708 --> 09:44.834
- Tozawa.

09:46.043 --> 09:49.630
- He's trying to prove
we can't protect our territory.

09:51.591 --> 09:52.466
We have to hit back.

09:54.885 --> 09:57.096
- And risk war?

09:57.888 --> 10:00.057
- But this is war.

10:00.558 --> 10:02.560
- We hit back,

10:02.643 --> 10:04.353
Chikara-kai will be seen
as the instigators,

10:04.437 --> 10:07.857
and the cops
will come down on us.

10:08.983 --> 10:09.483
Are you idiots?!

10:12.737 --> 10:15.656
No. No retaliation.

10:17.908 --> 10:19.660
For now, we increase
protection fees.

10:22.788 --> 10:25.958
We use the extra money
to close ranks and prepare.

10:28.336 --> 10:29.337
Kume...

10:29.420 --> 10:30.421
- Hai.

10:30.504 --> 10:31.505
- Kobayashi...

10:31.589 --> 10:31.672
- Hai.

10:32.715 --> 10:36.177
- If a war is coming
with Tozawa, we'll be ready.

10:44.060 --> 10:45.102
- Oyabun likes them
chopped fine.

10:45.603 --> 10:50.399
Tip stays on the board,
one smooth motion...

10:51.400 --> 10:52.902
- Damn, Sato.

10:54.362 --> 10:55.905
You think

10:55.988 --> 10:57.740
maybe you went
into the wrong business?

10:59.992 --> 11:03.120
Hope you're as good with
that knife outside the kitchen.

11:06.874 --> 11:07.792
- Should we go find out?

11:11.629 --> 11:11.712
- Sato.

11:17.134 --> 11:18.469
Go make the rounds.

11:19.220 --> 11:20.721
- They've already paid
this month.

11:22.139 --> 11:23.224
- Now they're paying more.

11:24.767 --> 11:24.850
- Okay.

11:34.485 --> 11:34.777
Don't fuck up the onions.

11:46.997 --> 11:48.249
- That bad, huh?

11:48.707 --> 11:50.459
- Be quiet.

11:55.214 --> 11:58.384
You need to stop using
so many adjectives.

12:00.177 --> 12:01.721
- Okay.

12:04.432 --> 12:07.101
It will run in
the morning edition.

12:11.856 --> 12:13.941
- Really?

12:14.024 --> 12:16.068
- You show initiative,
and this is real news.

12:16.152 --> 12:17.945
Keep it up.

12:20.614 --> 12:22.825
- Not bad, Jake-san.

12:22.908 --> 12:23.993
- That's my first article, man.

12:24.076 --> 12:24.702
Yeah, I know.

12:30.916 --> 12:33.919
Why do I feel like the greatest
investigative journalist

12:34.003 --> 12:35.463
that ever lived?

12:35.546 --> 12:37.298
Because you're an American,

12:37.381 --> 12:39.800
so you think you're more
talented than you actually are.

12:39.884 --> 12:41.802
- That's right.

12:45.097 --> 12:46.474
Or maybe I'm just lucky.

12:55.232 --> 12:57.526
What time do we have to be back
at the Meicho for Ko-etsu?

12:57.610 --> 13:02.531
About 90 minutes.

13:08.204 --> 13:11.582
Hey. We all have to do it.

13:11.665 --> 13:13.501
It's the final check, Jake.

13:15.628 --> 13:17.505
You can't be late. Hey!

14:00.673 --> 14:03.217
- Considering the evidence,

14:03.300 --> 14:05.928
and now this confession,
we expect an easy conviction.

14:08.180 --> 14:09.890
I hope this will bring
you and your family

14:09.974 --> 14:11.350
some measure of comfort.

14:21.902 --> 14:25.573
- Forgive me if this is
too painful to revisit but...

14:26.657 --> 14:28.075
I understand,

14:28.158 --> 14:29.076
from the statement
you gave Detective Funaki

14:29.159 --> 14:31.120
that your husband
was having financial problems.

14:32.580 --> 14:35.291
- I went through all this
with the other detectives.

14:36.041 --> 14:38.210
They didn't seem
to think it was relevant.

14:38.669 --> 14:39.211
- Of course.

14:40.170 --> 14:46.343
I'm just following up to ensure
nothing's been overlooked.

14:50.347 --> 14:52.641
- We borrowed.

14:53.559 --> 14:53.809
Too much.

14:56.103 --> 14:57.605
We missed one payment

14:57.688 --> 14:58.772
and the interest rate
became ten times higher.

15:00.524 --> 15:02.776
So my husband pushed back.

15:03.235 --> 15:04.194
- How so?

15:05.029 --> 15:09.408
- He was gathering information
to bring to a lawyer.

15:10.242 --> 15:12.578
About these lenders
and their...

15:12.661 --> 15:14.246
methods.

15:15.205 --> 15:19.126
- Do you happen to have
that information?

15:25.424 --> 15:26.675
- Yes.

15:43.942 --> 15:45.027
- May I help you?

15:46.612 --> 15:49.573
- My name is Jake Adelstein.
I'm with the Meicho Shimbun.

15:50.616 --> 15:53.994
- I'm sorry, I've been asked
not to speak with the press.

15:54.411 --> 15:55.954
- Really?

15:56.038 --> 15:58.082
But...

15:58.165 --> 16:00.167
just a few minutes is enough.

16:00.751 --> 16:01.543
May I have some of your time?

16:01.627 --> 16:02.961
- I'm afraid I have company...

16:11.512 --> 16:13.681
"Takahiro Aoki has borrowed
a large amount of money.

16:13.764 --> 16:17.101
"How do you feel
about a dirtbag like him

16:17.184 --> 16:18.852
living in your neighborhood?"

16:29.196 --> 16:31.532
- Well, then,
can I ask you one--

16:31.615 --> 16:34.076
- I have nothing to share.

16:37.746 --> 16:40.124
- I will come again.

16:41.959 --> 16:44.545
I'm sorry for bothering you.

16:45.796 --> 16:48.465
Once again,
my deepest condolences.

17:46.648 --> 17:47.941
- Hey, he looks like
real yakuza, right?

17:51.278 --> 17:52.738
- Wanna play?

18:01.538 --> 18:03.749
- He's gonna kill this.

18:18.680 --> 18:19.598
- Got you!

18:19.681 --> 18:20.724
You have two lives left.

18:20.808 --> 18:22.684
Reload!

18:22.768 --> 18:24.561
Got you!

18:24.645 --> 18:25.938
You have one life left.

18:28.148 --> 18:31.026
Got you! You're dead!

18:39.284 --> 18:40.953
- With my humble regards.

19:48.812 --> 19:50.898
- Oh!
- Ooh.

19:50.981 --> 19:53.150
- Oh sorry, I didn't expect--
- Malee.

19:53.233 --> 19:54.526
- Usually no one is here
so early.

19:54.610 --> 19:55.068
- What are you doing here?

19:55.152 --> 19:56.904
- I forgot my hair brush.

19:56.987 --> 19:58.572
- Malee, hurry up.

19:58.655 --> 20:00.073
I don't have much time today--

20:07.205 --> 20:07.956
- Ah,

20:08.040 --> 20:10.918
here's that hairbrush
that you forgot.

20:11.001 --> 20:12.961
Why don't you wait outside?
I'll give you a ride home.

20:15.589 --> 20:17.591
Classy.

20:19.676 --> 20:23.722
She's bad with customer,
so I give her lessons.

20:27.851 --> 20:30.604
Bitches who meddle
get sent back to America.

20:30.687 --> 20:33.523
- Don't fucking threaten me.
I have a work visa.

20:33.607 --> 20:35.400
- Try to fuck with me,

20:35.484 --> 20:37.235
I make one phone call,
and you're out of here.

20:37.319 --> 20:40.197
- And I walk out of here
with ten of your best girls.

20:40.280 --> 20:41.657
How will your business be then?

20:41.740 --> 20:42.199
Huh, Duke?

20:51.750 --> 20:52.125
- Go home, Samantha.

21:22.906 --> 21:24.366
- Where'd you go, Mossad?

21:24.449 --> 21:26.576
- Ah, had to make a quick stop
to fuck your mother.

21:26.660 --> 21:29.329
- What?

21:29.413 --> 21:31.206
Y-you fucked my mother?

21:33.500 --> 21:35.460
Jake-san, why did you do that?

21:35.544 --> 21:37.212
- No, not really.
In America, we--

21:38.880 --> 21:42.009
I got him.

21:43.093 --> 21:44.845
Those things stink.

21:44.928 --> 21:46.138
- They're French.

21:46.221 --> 21:48.307
- French people stink too.

21:48.390 --> 21:50.600
- That is not true.

21:50.684 --> 21:52.894
The French have
very good hygiene.

21:52.978 --> 21:55.939
Renaissance Europeans,
especially French aristocrats,

21:56.023 --> 21:58.859
believed that taking a bath--
- Okay, Tin-Tin.

21:58.942 --> 22:01.028
- Right.
- Tin-Tin.

22:01.111 --> 22:02.112
- I see that.

22:02.195 --> 22:04.364
- It's pronounced "Tahn-Than,"

22:04.448 --> 22:05.866
and he is Belgian.

22:05.949 --> 22:08.452
- Belgian, French,
same fucking thing.

22:08.535 --> 22:10.037
- First of all,
Belgium is a monarchy,

22:10.120 --> 22:11.288
and France is a republic.

22:11.371 --> 22:14.458
Okay, Tin-Tin.

22:14.541 --> 22:17.669
- Fuck you. Trendy Haiyu.

22:17.753 --> 22:18.503
Oh!

22:18.587 --> 22:19.921
A trendy actor, yeah?

22:20.005 --> 22:22.174
You got nice hair,
like an actor's.

22:25.844 --> 22:26.887
Gaijin!

22:27.637 --> 22:28.638
- Hai.

22:32.851 --> 22:33.518
- Read this. Out loud. Now.

22:33.602 --> 22:34.561
- Yes.

22:34.978 --> 22:38.398
Underwear thief...captured...

22:45.030 --> 22:48.200
- Today at30 p.m.,

22:48.283 --> 22:50.994
the Shinjuku police arrested an
office worker, age forty-one,

22:51.078 --> 22:52.913
a resident of Shinjuku-ward
Kabuki-cho Block 1,

22:52.996 --> 22:55.373
on charges of theft.

22:56.249 --> 22:59.503
The police raided his apartment
and found

22:59.586 --> 23:03.548
400 pairs of women's underwear,

23:03.632 --> 23:07.094
color-coded and sorted.

23:10.222 --> 23:13.183
But according to you,
there is no underwear thief.

23:19.356 --> 23:21.858
We can't trust you
to report one simple story.

23:29.199 --> 23:31.993
That's why you're shit.

23:32.577 --> 23:34.162
Go to scrapbooking.

23:34.246 --> 23:35.205
You're done here.

23:35.288 --> 23:35.330
- Hai.

23:48.218 --> 23:50.512
- Last time I checked,
Katagiri,

23:50.595 --> 23:52.305
loan sharks don't kill people,

23:55.225 --> 23:57.936
because dead men pay no debts.

23:58.019 --> 23:59.729
- You don't find it suspicious?

24:00.939 --> 24:03.817
